[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[i][b]Important — do not install alongside other inventory / storage / capacity mods.[/b] Where's Ma' Storage overrides inventory logic deeply. Mixing it with other mods that do the same (e.g. More Inventory Slots) produces duplicate entries, vanished piles, and empty vendor tabs. The mod detects More Inventory Slots specifically and disables it at the main menu with a warning, but other storage-modifying mods aren't guarded — uninstall them first.[/i]

[size=3]One shared inventory across every crafting station, bigger chests, and bigger stacks. No more running between racks to find the one bit of ore you need.[/size]

[size=3][b]Shared inventory[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3]Every container you've built — chests, racks, stockpiles, church bookcases, alchemy racks, organ racks, the keeper's room rack, and more — is pooled into one virtual inventory that every workstation can draw from.[/size]
[*][size=3]Works across zones. Craft at the farm with materials stored at the morgue, the lighthouse, or the tavern.[/size]
[*][size=3]Can be turned off entirely via the master "Shared Inventory" toggle if you'd rather play vanilla-style with just the other features.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Inventory size[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3]Two independent sliders — one for your player inventory, one for chests/racks/other containers. Want a tight player carry but huge chests? Now you can. (Before 2.1.14 there was a single combined slider.)[/size]
[*][size=3]Each slider is 0–a lot — zero means no change vs vanilla. Raising them grows every existing container in the world, not just newly-built ones.[/size]
[*][size=3]Reducing a slider below what you currently have stored pops up a Yes/No confirmation showing exactly how many items would no longer fit. Answer "Yes" to drop the overflow at your feet (for your inventory) or next to the container (for chests). Answer "No" to roll the slider back so nothing is touched.[/size]
[*][size=3]Save compatibility with older versions: if an earlier version of this mod ever silently hid items when shrinking, those items are revealed the next time you open the affected container. Nothing stays lost.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Stack sizes and stacking[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3]Raises the default per-item stack cap (max 999) so you can hoard without clutter. Configurable.[/size]
[*][size=3]Optional stacking for tools, weapons, armour, grave items, prayers, chisels, and pen/paper/ink items. Each category has its own toggle so you can stack only the ones you want.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Caveat on stacked tools/chisels/pens:[/b] when a durability-consuming item is stacked, the whole item gets spent in crafts instead of losing durability, and a damaged item placed on top of a fresh stack will "heal" to the fresh item's durability. If you're short on materials early game, leave these off. Late game when you're rich, turn them on. [b]This is intentional and not a bug.[/b][/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]UI options[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Show only personal inventory[/b] — optionally suppress the big shared list during vendor trades, tavern cellar access, chest transfers, the soul box, and the writer's table. Useful if you want those UIs to behave like vanilla.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Hide specific widget types[/b] — independently hide stockpiles, tavern containers, soul containers, and warehouse/shop widgets from the inventory list so the scroll is shorter. Refugee camp and pump/pallet widgets are always hidden (they'd add noise, not storage).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Hide invalid selections[/b] during crafting and selling so you only see items that are actually valid for the current task. If an inventory has zero valid items, that row is hidden entirely.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Hide empty rows[/b] in your inventory and chests — big performance boost with a lot of containers.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Remove section separators[/b] for a tighter, denser list.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Disable inventory greying[/b] during vendor trades (vanilla greys out items not in your personal inventory).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Show used/total slot count[/b] in each widget's title for at-a-glance space awareness.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]What's kept separate (intentional)[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Refugee inventories[/b] stay entirely outside the shared pool. Mixing them in breaks refugee logistics and was not the right call.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Quarry / Zombie Mill / Wells[/b] can each be independently excluded from the shared pool if you want zombies at those stations to have self-contained supplies. Toggle each in the config.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Vendor sides[/b] are untouched — WMS never pools a vendor's stock with yours.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Other quality-of-life[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3]New chests / racks added to the world (after building or moving) are picked up by the shared pool automatically — no restart, no reload.[/size]
[*][size=3]Optional "collect drops on game load" sweep picks up any items lying on the ground in the graveyard when you load a save.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Main menu update notice[/b] flags when a newer version of this mod (or other mods in my collection) is available on Nexus. Click an entry to open its Nexus page. Opt-out via the "Check for Updates" setting.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/64]Gerry's Junk Trunk[/url] — a buildable trunk that Gerry sells items from for you. Progression-gated and pairs nicely with WMS's shared inventory: stash via WMS, dump excess in the trunk.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/61]Beam Me Up Gerry[/url] — teleport between the zones you've visited with Z / RB. Great when your stuff is spread across regions.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/51]Auto-Loot Heavies[/url] — teleports timber, stone, marble, and ore to the nearest stockpile with space. Feed the shared pool without manual trips.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/70]Give Me Moar[/url] — multipliers for drops and craft outputs across the game. Fills shared storage even faster.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

